File: The news was confirmed on Monday morning by the Nelson Mandela Foundation. * Editor's note: This is a developing story. JOHANNESBURG - Zindziswa "Zindzi" Mandela has died at the age of 59. The news was confirmed on Monday morning by the Nelson Mandela Foundation. READ: With freedom comes responsibility - Zindzi Mandela The daughter of former President Nelson Mandela and Winnie Madikizela-Mandela served as South Africa's ambassador to Denmark. Mandela is survived by her four children and her husband. Cosatu general-secretary Bheki Ntshalintshali paid tribute to Zindzi Mandela.